    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - WATER PUMP AND THERMOSTAT - WATER PUMP - INSTALLATION</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a new gasket, place the gasket over the water pump housing dowels. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151019">10.19</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the water pump to the front cover. Tighten the mounting bolts and washers to the
                specified standard torque. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151020">10.20</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be sure the water pump rotates freely after installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4151018" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg5980" filename="../figcg5/CG5980.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.18. Press on Impeller and Check Impeller to Housing Clearance.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4151019" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12218" filename="../figcg1/CG12218.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.19. Align Gasket onto Water Pump Dowels.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4151020" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12219" filename="../figcg1/CG12219.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.20. Install the Water Pump.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the water pump pulley over the water pump hub. Fasten the pulley to the hub using the
                six mounting bolts and washers. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_228.xml" xrefid="ef4151021">10.21</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Tighten to the standard torque while using a pry bar to prevent pulley movement.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
